<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. A. Le, D. Dien &amp; Tagane. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[318,548,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aroangensis">
<emphasis box="[318,548,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Thottea aroangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found on alluvial soils of the shady reclined slope in primary broad-leaved evergreen forest at elevation around 
<quantity box="[537,606,194,221]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="m" value="850.0">850 m</quantity>
a.s.l., where it grows with 
<taxonomicName authority="Aver., Tillich &amp; T. A. Le" authorityName="Aver., Tillich &amp; T. A. Le" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aspidistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="heterocarpa" variety="echinata">
<emphasis box="[900,1156,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Aspidistra heterocarpa</emphasis>
Aver., Tillich &amp; V.T. Pham var. 
<emphasis box="[186,282,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">echinata</emphasis>
Aver., Tillich &amp; T.A. Le
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[581,736,230,257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Hypoxidaceae" genus="Curculigo" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[581,694,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Curculigo</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Roxb." authorityName="Roxb." box="[750,1084,230,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Dracaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[750,1005,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Dracaena angustifolia</emphasis>
Roxb.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gaertn.) Kanis." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ochnaceae" genus="Gomphia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[1147,1341,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Gomphia serrata</emphasis>
(Gaertn.) Kanis.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,941]" box="[189,993,302,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,302,328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Flowering in March to April and fruiting in April to May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,338,364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from its 
<typeStatus box="[791,839,339,365]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">type</typeStatus>
locality, A Roang commune, located in A Luoi district, Thua Thien Hue province, central 
<collectingCountry box="[521,620,374,400]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,941]" box="[189,610,410,439]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,433,410,436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Vernacular name:—</emphasis>
Tốt hoa a roàng
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,672,446,472]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Preliminary conservation assessment:—</emphasis>
Critically Endangered (CR). To date, we found only five individuals in one population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. A. Le, D. Dien &amp; Tagane. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[368,597,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aroangensis">
<emphasis box="[368,597,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Thottea aroangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[673,721,483,509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">type</typeStatus>
locality. Therefore, the most appropriate initial assessment of the IUCN conservation status for this species is Critically Endangered (CR) under criteria D (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[1137,1282,518,544]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refId="ref2285" refString="IUCN (2012) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: version 3.1, second edition. IUCN: Gland and Cambridge." type="book" year="2012">IUCN, 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The habitat is located within the protected area at district level and well-protected. However, since it grows near the route for tourist, we need to pay special attention for its survival.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,283,626,652]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Note:—</emphasis>
In Indochina, three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rottboll" authorityYear="1783" box="[622,708,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[622,708,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Thottea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hou" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Loureiro" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[722,859,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis box="[722,859,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hou" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Blume 1827:" baseAuthorityYear="1135" box="[873,1016,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis box="[873,1016,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hou" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Merrill &amp; Chun" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1078,1285,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[1078,1099,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T.</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis box="[1151,1285,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were recorded (
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, D." box="[144,263,662,688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="301 - 321" refId="ref2128" refString="Hou, D. (1981) Florae Malesianae Praecursores LXII on the genus Thottea (Aristolochiaceae). Blumea 27: 301 - 321." type="journal article" year="1981">Hou 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ho, P. H." box="[279,383,662,688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refId="ref2097" refString="Ho, P. H. (1999) Cay Co Viet Nam: An Illustrated Flora of Vietnam, vol. 1. Published by the author, Montreal." type="book" year="1999">Hô 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Phan, K. L. &amp; Nguyen, T. H. &amp; Nguyen Q. H. &amp; Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Nguyen, S. K." box="[398,595,662,688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="200 - 206" refId="ref2505" refString="Phan, K. L., Nguyen, T. H., Nguyen Q. H., Averyanov, L. V. &amp; Nguyen, S. K. (2009) New records of genera and species for the flora of Vietnam. Proceedings of the 3 rd National Scientific Conference on Ecology and Biological Resources: 200 - 206." type="proceedings paper" year="2009">
Phan 
<emphasis box="[465,525,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tagane, S. &amp; Souladeth, P. &amp; Rueangruea, S. &amp; Okabe, N. &amp; Zhang, M. &amp; Chayer, S. &amp; Yang, C. - J. &amp; Yahara, T." box="[610,833,662,689]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="107 - 116" refId="ref2786" refString="Tagane, S., Souladeth, P., Rueangruea, S., Okabe, N., Zhang, M., Chayer, S., Yang, C. - J. &amp; Yahara, T. (2017) Flora of Nam Kading National Protected Area II: 30 new records of angiosperms for Laos. Edinburgh Journal of Botany 75: 107 - 116. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0960428617000361" type="journal article" year="2017">
Tagane 
<emphasis box="[701,761,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. A. Le, D. Dien &amp; Tagane. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[855,1088,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aroangensis">
<emphasis box="[855,1088,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Thottea aroangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hou" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Loureiro" baseAuthorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hou" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Merrill &amp; Chun" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[303,513,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[303,324,699,724]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T.</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis box="[379,513,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its inflorescence at base of stem close to ground level (vs. at the upper part of stem, in the axils of foliage leaves) and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hou" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Blume 1827:" baseAuthorityYear="1135" box="[655,799,735,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis box="[655,799,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by taller habit 
<quantity box="[974,1087,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="80.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="70.0">70–90 cm</quantity>
tall (vs. 
<quantity box="[1189,1301,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="30.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="10.0">10–50 cm</quantity>
tall), abaxial surface of lamina sparsely pubescent along midrib and veins (vs. tomentose), and longer perianth ca. 
<quantity box="[1270,1346,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="2.6">2.6 cm</quantity>
long (vs. 
<quantity box="[136,261,806,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.7">0.7–1.2 cm</quantity>
long). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. A. Le, D. Dien &amp; Tagane. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[341,569,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aroangensis">
<emphasis box="[341,569,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Thottea aroangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hou (1981: 315)" authorityName="Hou" authorityPageNumber="315" authorityYear="1981" box="[715,1026,806,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="becarrii">
<emphasis box="[715,832,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. becarrii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, D." box="[840,1026,806,833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="301 - 321" refId="ref2128" refString="Hou, D. (1981) Florae Malesianae Praecursores LXII on the genus Thottea (Aristolochiaceae). Blumea 27: 301 - 321." type="journal article" year="1981">Hou (1981: 315)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingRegion box="[1063,1156,806,832]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
in having inflorescence at base of stems and obscurely lobed perianth, but differs in having smaller lamina (13–16 × 
<quantity box="[1165,1249,842,869]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. A. Le, D. Dien &amp; Tagane. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[1287,1451,843,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aroangensis">
<emphasis box="[1287,1451,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. aroangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 19.5–25 × 
<quantity box="[304,425,878,905]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.225" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.95" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="12.25" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="9.5">9.5–15 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[466,600,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Thottea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beccarrii">
<emphasis box="[466,600,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">T. beccarrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), shorter pedicle and ovary (
<quantity box="[935,1046,878,905]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="5.0">5–12 mm</quantity>
long vs. 
<quantity box="[1157,1301,878,905]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.625" metricValueMax="1.75" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="16.25" valueMax="17.5" valueMin="15.0">15–17.5 mm</quantity>
long), larger campanulate perianth ca. 
<quantity box="[422,498,914,941]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="2.6">2.6 cm</quantity>
long (vs. perianth cupular, 
<quantity box="[806,931,914,941]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 cm</quantity>
long).
</paragraph>
